; MODESWITCH corner cases: a @differential message chained through several
; locals nests removal-mode switches inside removal-mode contexts (inner
; switch as sole body of outer switch; re-assertion of the mode already in
; effect), plus a top-level switch to the default addition mode. The unused
; local gives a switch whose body is DCE'd first (empty-body switch left
; for RemoveUnused).

#message add(i32 A) @differential.
#local a(i32 A).
#local b(i32 A).
#local c(i32 A).
#local dead(i32 A).
#query q(free i32 A).

a(A) : add(A).
b(A) : a(A).
c(A) : b(A).
dead(A) : add(A).
q(A) : c(A).
